### SmartAid REST tests — Audit Logs (Phase 7)
###
### Covers GET /api/audit-logs (admin only) with:
###   filters: user_id, action, entity_type, entity_id, from, to
###   pagination: limit (default 50, max 500), offset
###   response shape: { filters, pagination: {limit, offset, total}, audit_logs: [...] }
###
### The audit_logger middleware auto-fires on every 2xx response for
### POST / PUT / PATCH / DELETE (except /api/auth/login). This file first
### triggers a few writes so we have fresh, predictable rows to filter on,
### then runs through every filter + pagination + error case.
###
### Run top-to-bottom. Re-running the SETUP block as-is may collide on
### unique email/phone — rerun migrations + seed if you need a clean slate
### (see tests/README.md).

@host = http://localhost:3000

### Login as admin
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@smartaid.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Login as shop_manager (used for 403 check)
# @name loginManager
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "manager@smartaid.com",
  "password": "manager123"
}

### Login as donor (used for 403 check)
# @name loginDonor
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "donor1@smartaid.com",
  "password": "donor123"
}

#######################################################################
### SETUP — trigger writes so we have fresh audit rows to filter on.
### Each successful 2xx write here adds exactly one audit_logs row.
#######################################################################

### SETUP 1 — Create a donor user (logs: CREATE_USER, entity_type=user)
# @name createDonor
POST {{host}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "REST Audit Donor",
  "email": "rest-audit-donor@smartaid.com",
  "password": "donor123",
  "role": "donor"
}

### SETUP 2 — Update that donor (logs: UPDATE_USER, entity_id={{createDonor.id}})
PUT {{host}}/api/users/{{createDonor.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "REST Audit Donor (renamed)"
}

### SETUP 3 — Create a beneficiary (logs: CREATE_BENEFICIARY, entity_type=beneficiary)
# @name createBen
POST {{host}}/api/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "REST Audit Ben",
  "phone_number": "+252-REST-AUDIT-1",
  "family_size": 3,
  "location": "Mogadishu"
}

### SETUP 4 — Update that beneficiary (logs: UPDATE_BENEFICIARY, entity_id={{createBen.id}})
PUT {{host}}/api/beneficiaries/{{createBen.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "family_size": 5
}

### SETUP 5 — Delete the donor (logs: DELETE_USER, entity_id={{createDonor.id}})
DELETE {{host}}/api/users/{{createDonor.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### LIST — no filters
#######################################################################

### 1) List audit logs as admin (no filters, default pagination)
# Expected: 200
# Shape: { filters, pagination: { limit: 50, offset: 0, total }, audit_logs: [...] }
# audit_logs[0] should be the most recent write (latest id DESC). Each row
# carries: id, user_id, user_email, user_role, action, entity_type, entity_id, logged_at.
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### FILTER — by user_id
#######################################################################

### 2) Filter by user_id=1 (admin user from seed)
# Expected: 200, every row has user_id=1 (all SETUP writes were as admin)
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?user_id=1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 3) Filter by user_id that has no writes
# Expected: 200, audit_logs = [], pagination.total = 0
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?user_id=9999
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### FILTER — by action
#######################################################################

### 4) Filter by action=CREATE_USER
# Expected: 200, every row has action='CREATE_USER'
#           SETUP 1 should appear in the results
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?action=CREATE_USER
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 5) Filter by action=UPDATE_BENEFICIARY
# Expected: 200, every row has action='UPDATE_BENEFICIARY'
#           SETUP 4 should appear in the results
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?action=UPDATE_BENEFICIARY
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 6) Filter by action=DELETE_USER
# Expected: 200, every row has action='DELETE_USER'
#           SETUP 5 should appear in the results
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?action=DELETE_USER
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 7) Filter by action that does not exist
# Expected: 200, audit_logs = [], total = 0
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?action=CREATE_NONEXISTENT
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### FILTER — by entity_type
#######################################################################

### 8) Filter by entity_type=user
# Expected: 200, every row has entity_type='user'
#           SETUP 1, 2, 5 should appear
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?entity_type=user
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 9) Filter by entity_type=beneficiary
# Expected: 200, every row has entity_type='beneficiary'
#           SETUP 3, 4 should appear
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?entity_type=beneficiary
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### FILTER — by entity_id
#######################################################################

### 10) Filter by entity_id = the donor we created (SETUP 1)
# Expected: 200, returns CREATE_USER + UPDATE_USER + DELETE_USER on that id
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?entity_id={{createDonor.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 11) Combined: entity_type=user AND entity_id=<created donor>
# Expected: 200, narrower than #10 (same rows, since all on user entity)
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?entity_type=user&entity_id={{createDonor.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 12) Combined: action=UPDATE_BENEFICIARY AND entity_id=<created ben>
# Expected: 200, returns just SETUP 4
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?action=UPDATE_BENEFICIARY&entity_id={{createBen.response.body.data.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### FILTER — by date range
### NOTE: dates below assume today is 2026-05-21. Update if you run on
### a different day (or use the same pattern as 08_reports.http).
#######################################################################

### 13) Date range — today only
# Expected: 200, includes all SETUP rows (they were inserted today)
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?from=2026-05-21T00:00:00Z&to=2026-05-21T23:59:59Z
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 14) Date range — far past (year 2000)
# Expected: 200, audit_logs = [], total = 0
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?from=2000-01-01T00:00:00Z&to=2000-12-31T23:59:59Z
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 15) Only `from` (open-ended upper bound)
# Expected: 200, all rows from that point onward
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?from=2026-01-01T00:00:00Z
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 16) Only `to` (open-ended lower bound)
# Expected: 200, all rows up to that point
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?to=2026-12-31T23:59:59Z
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### PAGINATION
#######################################################################

### 17) Pagination — limit=1
# Expected: 200, audit_logs.length == 1, pagination.total = full count
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?limit=1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 18) Pagination — limit=2 offset=1
# Expected: 200, returns the 2nd & 3rd rows (latest-id DESC)
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?limit=2&offset=1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 19) Pagination — limit above MAX_LIMIT (500) is clamped to 500
# Expected: 200, pagination.limit == 500
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?limit=9999
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### BAD INPUT — 400 cases
#######################################################################

### 20) user_id is not an integer
# Expected: 400 { "error": "user_id must be a positive integer" }
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?user_id=abc
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 21) user_id is negative
# Expected: 400
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?user_id=-1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 22) entity_id is not an integer
# Expected: 400 { "error": "entity_id must be a positive integer" }
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?entity_id=xyz
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 23) from is not a valid date
# Expected: 400 { "error": "from must be a valid date" }
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?from=not-a-date
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 24) to is not a valid date
# Expected: 400 { "error": "to must be a valid date" }
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?to=garbage
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 25) limit is negative
# Expected: 400 { "error": "limit must be a positive integer" }
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?limit=-5
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 26) limit is zero
# Expected: 400 (controller requires limit > 0)
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?limit=0
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 27) offset is negative
# Expected: 400 { "error": "offset must be a non-negative integer" }
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?offset=-1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### AUTH / ROLE GUARDS
#######################################################################

### 28) No token
# Expected: 401
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs

### 29) As donor
# Expected: 403 { "error": "Forbidden: insufficient role" }
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{loginDonor.response.body.data.token}}

### 30) As shop_manager
# Expected: 403 { "error": "Forbidden: insufficient role" }
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{loginManager.response.body.data.token}}

#######################################################################
### SELF-CHECK — confirm the GET above did NOT add an audit_logs row
### (audit_logger only fires on write methods). Re-list after one of the
### list calls; total should not have grown beyond what SETUP produced.
#######################################################################

### 31) Final list — total should match what we had earlier
# Expected: pagination.total identical to what #1 returned
GET {{host}}/api/audit-logs?limit=1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
